&lt;p&gt;Cardiothoracic Outpatient Specialist nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, motivated Band 6 nurse to join the Cardiothoracic Outpatients nursing team. You will support the Outpatient service, and participate in the nurse-led Rapid Access Chest Pain, Post PCI follow up and Perhexiline clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have extensive experience in cardiac nursing, excellent communication and interpersonal skills, along with an ability to work flexibly to meet the demands of the service. You will need to work autonomously, and as part of the Outpatient team, demonstrating clinical patient assessment skills. We are looking for a dynamic individual who shares the vision for this service, and who will contribute to the progression of nurse-led services, including new pathways and developments within the Cardiac Imaging Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are searching for nurses who share our values that:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;•We care about the people we serve and the people we work with&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;•We trust one another&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;•We respect each other&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;•We take personal responsibility&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;•We treat people with kindness&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;•We act with integrity&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In return we will offer you a dynamic, friendly working environment, a full induction programme and an individual personal development plan to guide your development within the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 18/11/2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Catrin Dix&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Catrin Dix &lt;br /&gt;02920 743266 &lt;br /&gt;catrin.dix@wales.nhs.uk &lt;/p&gt;
